translated: Billkvist, Tore Elias Albrekt, practicing physician, Gothenburg, b. 29/11/05 in Falun to grocer August B. and Nanny Lundberg. Married to Gerd Larsison in the year 19xx. Children: Gerd Gudrun b. 37, Inger b. 39, Kerstin b. 42. Studied for the studentexamen in Örebro in 1925, received a degree in medicine from Uppsala in 1929, and acquired a medical license in Stockholm in 1933. Was an assistant physician and temporary deputy head physician at Serafimerlasarettet ear clinic in 1933, assistant physician and deputy physician at the surgical department of Kronprinsessan Lovisa hospital, as well as temporary deputy physician at Mariestads hospital in 1934, deputy physician at Serafimerlasarettet ear clinic and Stockholm's Stocksund hospital ear department in 1936-1937, temporary assistant physician at Serafimerlasarettet ear clinic in 1937-1938, deputy physician at Sabbatsbergs hospital ear department in 1938, and the same position at Sahlgrrenska hospital from 1938-1943. Consulted as a physician for the pediatric hospital for ear, nose, and throat diseases in Gothenburg since 1944, and was manager for the ear, nose, and throat clinic in Redbergslid from 1944 onwards.
